     <iframe  width="1024" height="576" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/W3O0-odGFXQ" title="" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold my-4">Tashakkur  quyidagi qismlardan iborat bo`ladi:</p>
<p><b>1.  Greeting (salomlashish).</b> Xatni <i>Dear Sir or Madam</i> (hurmatli janob yoki xonim) bilan boshlang. Yozib bo`lgach vergul(,) qo`yiladi.
<p><b>2.  Introduction (kirish qismi).</b> Maktubingizni nima maqsadda, ya`ni nima uchun  yozayotganligingizni ko`rsating.</p>
<p><b>3.  Body (ma`no qismi).</b> Siz uchun qilgan ishi sizning nazdingizda qanchalik qadrli va ahamiyatli ekanligini bildirishingiz kerak. O`z rahmatingizni ayting va buning evaziga nima qilmoqchiligingizni keltiring. Yakunlashda ba`zi bir iboralar bilan minnatdorchiligingizni bildiring yoki aloqani davom ettirish niyatingiz borligini bildiring.</p>
<p><b>4.  Closing (yakuniy qism):</b> Agar xatni <i>“Dear Sir” yoki “Dear Mam”</i> bilan boshlagan bo`lsangiz <i>“Yours faithfully”</i> (faqat birinchi harfini katta harf bilan yozasiz), agar xatni oluvchining ismi bilan boshlagan bo`lsangiz <i>“Yours sincerely”</i> yoki <i>“Sincerely yours”</i> bilan yakunlang. Ismingizni yozishingiz shart emas.</p>


<ul class="list-disc my-3"> 
  <b class="text-lg">Tavsiyalar:</b>
<li>Faqat maqsadingiz haqida yozing.</li>
<li>Samimiy ma`noda yozing.</li>
<li>Xatingizni tushunarli yozing. Voqealar tafsilotlarini aniq qilib kiriting.</li>
<li>Xatni yakunlashda iboralardan foydalaning. Qanday yakunlash tashakkur xatining turiga bog`liq.</li>
</ul>

<p class="bg-blue-200 p-3 rounded"><b>Note:</b> Har bir kishi ularning mehribonligini qadrlashingizni aytiladigan xatlarni yoqtirishadilar. Yaxshi va iliq fikrlarni ifodalavchi xatlarga har qanday kishi ijobiy munosabatda bo`ladi.</p>
</p>
<h3 class="text-lg text-center font-bold mt-3">Sample Letter Analysis</h3>
<section class="border border-gray-800 p-3 my-3">
<div><b>You should spend about 20 minutes on this task.</b><div>
  <div><b><i>You are a commuter. One morning on your way to work you suddenly fell ill and lost your consciousness. One gentleman on the same bus sent you to a hospital. Write a letter to the company where the gentleman works to extend your gratefulness.</i></b></div>
<p><b>You should write at least 150 words.
You do NOT need to write your address.
Begin your letter as follows:<br>
Dear Sir or Madam,</b></p>
</section>

<p>Dear Sir or Madam,<br>
I am writing this letter to extend my sincere thanks to Mr. Baker, the cashier of your company.<br>
I am a commuter and every day I take bus Route 133 to work. Last Friday morning when the bus almost reached the stop where I was to get off, I suddenly felt dizzy and  vthen I lost my consciousness. When I came to, I found myself in St. Mary’s Hospital, attended by my wife. The doctor told me it was Mr. Baker who had sent me to the hospital and informed my wife of my condition. Mr. Baker happened to be on the same bus, but I have never met him.<br>
My wife and I were very much grateful to Mr. Baker for his kindness. Please forward my heartfelt thankfulness to him. We feel very much proud of your company for having such a good employee. If Mr. Baker was late for work that day, I’d like to compensate you.<br>
I do hope that your company would reward Mr. Baker for his noble deeds.<br>
Yours faithfully,<br>
Larry Smith
</p>

<h3 class="text-lg text-center font-bold mt-4">Namunaviy xat tahlili:</h3>
<p>Ushbu namunaviy xatda yuqorida aytib o'tilgan to'rtta asosiy qismni o'z ichiga olganligini ko'rishingiz mumkin.</p>
<ol>
<li><b>Greeting (salomlashish).</b> “Dear Sir or Madam” bilan boshlangan (yuqorida yuriqnomada aytilgandek). Vergul qo`yilgan.</li>
<li><b>Introduction (kirish qismi).</b> Xatda xatning yozilishi sababi aytilgan.</li>
<li><b>Body (ma`no qismi).</b>  O‘zi bilan bo‘lgan voqea aytilgan. Keyin u janob Beykerga o'z minnatdorchiligi va uning kompaniyasiga taklifi bildiradi (ya'ni janob Beykerni mukofotlash).</li>
<li><b>Closing (yakuniy qism):</b> O`rinli bo`lgan xatni yakunlavchi iboradan foydalanilgan. Ismni yozish va imzo qo`yish shart emas.</li>
</ol>
